@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About";
    ViewBag.Message = "Learn More About the Library Management System";
}

<style>
    body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        background-color: #f5f5f5;
        color: #333;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 20px;
    }

    .about-container {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        background-color: #fff;
        padding: 40px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        box-shadow: 0px 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    h2 {
        color: #2c3e50;
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    h3 {
        color: #555;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    p {
        line-height: 1.6;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        color: #666;
    }
</style>

<div class="about-container">
    <h2>@ViewBag.Title</h2>
    <h3>@ViewBag.Message</h3>

    <p>The Library Management System is a user-focused application designed in ASP.NET MVC with an MSSQL backend. It provides a comprehensive solution for managing library operations efficiently. The system offers distinct modules for both administrators and library users, making it easy for admins to manage the book catalog and for users to browse and borrow books effortlessly.</p>

    <p>This platform aims to deliver a smooth and organized library experience, ensuring secure access and an intuitive interface. It empowers library administrators with tools to add, update, and manage books, while giving users the convenience of exploring the library’s collection and borrowing items seamlessly. With this system, library interactions become more accessible and enjoyable for all users.</p>
</div>
